long_description:
Step 1: Ask user for setting key and value
Step 2: POST /api/settings with X-Workspace-Id header and { key, value }
Step 3: Confirm setting saved

Step 1: Ask for workspace id and new name (or list workspaces first)
Step 2: PUT /api/workspaces with { id, name }
Step 3: Confirm workspace renamed

Step 1: Ask for clip_id (or show pending clips list first)
Step 2: PATCH /api/clips/status with X-Workspace-Id header: { clip_id, status: 'approved' }
Step 3: Confirm clip approved and ready for publishing

Step 1: Ask for clip_id (or show pending clips list first)
Step 2: PATCH /api/clips/status with X-Workspace-Id header: { clip_id, status: 'rejected' }
Step 3: Confirm clip rejected

Step 1: Ask for clip_id and target status (pending_review | approved | rejected)
Step 2: PATCH /api/clips/status with X-Workspace-Id header: { clip_id, status }
Step 3: Confirm status updated

Step 1: Ask for article id (or list draft articles first)
Step 2: POST /api/articles/approve with X-Workspace-Id header: { id }
Step 3: Confirm article status changed to approve

Step 1: Ask for article id
Step 2: POST /api/articles/reject with X-Workspace-Id header: { id }
Step 3: Confirm article rejected

Step 1: Ask for article id
Step 2: POST /api/articles/draft with X-Workspace-Id header: { id }
Step 3: Confirm article moved back to draft for editing

Step 1: Ask for article id — must be in approve status
Step 2: POST /api/articles/publish with X-Workspace-Id header: { id }
Step 3: Confirm article status set to published

Step 1: Ask for article id and target status (draft | approve | rejected | published)
Step 2: PATCH /api/articles/status with X-Workspace-Id header: { id, status }
Step 3: Confirm status updated

Step 1: Ask for post id and action (approve | reject | publish)
Step 2: PUT /api/social-posts with X-Workspace-Id header: { id, action }
Step 3: Confirm status updated (approve→approved, reject→rejected, publish→published)

Step 1: Ask for publication id and action (activate | deactivate)
Step 2: PATCH /api/publications with { id, action }
Step 3: Confirm status toggled

Step 1: Ask for idea id and fields to update
Step 2: PUT /api/ideas with { id, ...fields }
Step 3: Confirm update successful

Step 1: Ask for bookmark id and fields to update
Step 2: PUT /api/bookmarks with { id, ...fields }
Step 3: Confirm update successful

Step 1: Ask for business name (required); optionally column names (default: Marketing, Follow-up, Research, Delivery)
Step 2: POST /api/businesses with { action: 'add', name, columns }
Step 3: Confirm business created

Step 1: Ask for asset id and fields to update (title, description, category, status, tags)
Step 2: PUT /api/assets with { id, ...fields }
Step 3: Confirm update successful

Step 1: Ask for name (required) and optional description
Step 2: POST /api/memory-banks with { name, description }
Step 3: Confirm memory bank created — starts with empty content array

Step 1: Ask for project name (required) and optional hex color
Step 2: POST /api/team/projects with { name, color }
Step 3: Confirm project created — now tasks can be added to this project

Step 1: Ask for project id and fields to update (name, color)
Step 2: PUT /api/team/projects with { id, name?, color? }
Step 3: Confirm update successful

Step 1: Ask for task id and fields to update
Step 2: PUT /api/team/tasks with { id, ...fields }
Step 3: Confirm update successful

Step 1: Ask for command id and fields to update (name, description, long_description, category, tags)
Step 2: PUT /api/commands with { id, ...fields }
Step 3: Confirm update successful

Step 1: Ask for item id and fields to update
Step 2: PUT /api/shopping with { id, ...fields }
Step 3: Confirm update successful
